# Docker Training Projects - 10 Projects Challenge

A collection of practical projects to learn and master Docker, completed as part of my backend training.

## Completed Projects:

### 1. Static Website Hosting with Nginx

- **Description:** Containerized and hosted a simple static HTML website using a lightweight Nginx image.
- **How to Run:**
  ```bash
  cd 01-static-website
  docker build -t my-static-website .
  docker run -d -p 8080:80 my-static-website
  Result:
  ```

2. Jekyll Jam – Static Site Playground
   Description: Containerized a Jekyll environment to build and preview a static website using Markdown, avoiding the need to install Ruby and Jekyll locally.

How to Run:

Bash
cd 02-jekyll-jam
docker build -t my-jekyll-site .
docker run -d -p 4000:4000 --name jekyll-container my-jekyll-site
Result:
